**The main problem**

It looks like you are trying to drag the ```LinearLayout``` up
But do not define ```motion:touchAnchorId=&quot;@+id/linearLayout&quot;```
```xml
        &lt;OnSwipe 
            app:touchAnchorSide=&quot;top&quot;
            app:touchAnchorId=&quot;@+id/linearLayout&quot;
         /&gt;

```
additional OnSwipe arguments would modify the default behavior.
Based on preferences.
  
**Secondary problem**

Looking at only attributes. You are going from:
```XML
    
        &lt;ImageView
            android:layout_height=&quot;0dp&quot;
            android:layout_height=&quot;0dp&quot;
            app:layout_constraintBottom_toTopOf=&quot;@+id/linearLayout&quot;
            app:layout_constraintTop_toTopOf=&quot;parent&quot; /&gt;

        &lt;LinearLayout
            android:layout_height=&quot;150dp&quot;
            app:layout_constraintBottom_toBottomOf=&quot;parent&quot;
            app:layout_constraintTop_toBottomOf=&quot;parent&quot;/&gt;
   

```

to 

```XML
    &lt;ImageView
        android:layout_height=&quot;0dp&quot;
        app:layout_constraintBottom_toTopOf=&quot;@+id/linearLayout&quot;
        app:layout_constraintTop_toTopOf=&quot;parent&quot; /&gt;

    &lt;LinearLayout
        android:layout_height=&quot;wrap_content&quot;
        app:layout_constraintBottom_toBottomOf=&quot;parent&quot;/&gt;
```

The ```LinearLayout``` goes from 50% below the screen to  wrap_content. I am not sure what is meant to happen here.
There are many possible effects you want.

If you want to hide extra off screen you could have the start look like this
```xml
 &lt;LinearLayout
        android:layout_height=&quot;wrap_content&quot;
        android:layout_marginTop=&quot;-75dp&quot;
        app:layout_constraintTop_toBottomOf=&quot;parent&quot;/&gt;
```
But there are many possibilities.

