----------


TestNG
------
[TestNG](https://testng.org/doc/documentation-main.html) is an annotation-based test framework which needs a marker annotation type to indicate that a method is a test method, and should be run by the testing tool. Hence, while using [tag:testng] as you use [annotations](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/1.5.0/docs/guide/language/annotations.html) and you don&#39;t have to call the `main()` method explicitly.


