answers.body_markdown:
yes, @Ilya correctly mentioned the [Freemarker docs][1] which state that there used to exist a fourth hash named ```RequestParameters```. 
And the minimalistic change to make it work, would be to change to ```org.springframework.ui.Model``` 

And @Damir is also correct: **Spring Boot 3+** (and consequently Spring Framework 6+) **breaks Freemarker**. Check @Neets comment on his answer. I suspect they won&#39;t be introducing a fix (soon).

And here&#39;s the workaround where you fetch the param from the URI if you don&#39;t want to use ```@RequestParam```: 
```
    @GetMapping(&quot;/signup&quot;)
    public String signupEndpoint(HttpServletRequest servletRequest, Model model) {
        // relating to your question, you&#39;d substitute &quot;parameterName&quot; in this method by &quot;name&quot;
        String urlParam = servletRequest.getParameter(&quot;parameterName&quot;);

        // make sure that the param isn&#39;t null. Freemarker will always throw an error
        if (null == urlParam) {
            urlParam = &quot;urlParam was empty!&quot;;
        }

        // provided you called http://localhost:8080/signup?name=rahul 
        // the variable urlParam would be initialized with value &quot;rahul&quot;
        // Spring will use the Model to populate your html
        model.addAttribute(&quot;parameterName&quot;, urlParam);
        return &quot;signup&quot;;
    }
```



  [1]: https://freemarker.apache.org/docs/pgui_misc_servlet.html

